and the mm are the same mm.

00:03:55.090 --> 00:04:00.740 align:middle line:84%
And then the ah and the
ugh are just little things.

00:04:00.740 --> 00:04:02.740 align:middle line:84%
They're the morning glories
opening and closing.

00:04:02.740 --> 00:04:09.780 align:middle line:90%


00:04:09.780 --> 00:04:14.780 align:middle line:84%
Remember the story of
the man, the farmer?

00:04:14.780 --> 00:04:18.560 align:middle line:90%
And one day his horse ran away.

00:04:18.560 --> 00:04:24.680 align:middle line:84%
And his neighbor said to
him, oh, that's too bad.

00:04:24.680 --> 00:04:28.850 align:middle line:90%
And the farmer said, who knows?

00:04:28.850 --> 00:04:31.520 align:middle line:84%
And the next day
the horse came back,

00:04:31.520 --> 00:04:34.250 align:middle line:84%
and it had attracted
a wild horse.

00:04:34.250 --> 00:04:36.650 align:middle line:90%
So now he had two horses.

00:04:36.650 --> 00:04:40.550 align:middle line:84%
And the neighbor came
and said, How wonderful!

00:04:40.550 --> 00:04:44.760 align:middle line:90%
And the farmer said, who knows?

00:04:44.760 --> 00:04:50.550 align:middle line:84%
And the next day, his young son
decided to ride the wild horse.

00:04:50.550 --> 00:04:53.040 align:middle line:84%
And he was riding the wild
horse, and he fell off

00:04:53.040 --> 00:04:54.630 align:middle line:90%
and he broke his leg.

00:04:54.630 --> 00:04:57.400 align:middle line:84%
And the neighbor came
and said, that's too bad.

00:04:57.400 --> 00:05:00.310 align:middle line:90%
And he said, who knows?

00:05:00.310 --> 00:05:04.320 align:middle line:84%
At the time there was a war,
and the army came through,

00:05:04.320 --> 00:05:06.570 align:middle line:90%
conscripting young men.

00:05:06.570 --> 00:05:10.260 align:middle line:84%
But they didn't take his son,
because he had a broken leg.

00:05:10.260 --> 00:05:12.360 align:middle line:84%
And the neighbors
said, how fortunate.

00:05:12.360 --> 00:05:15.000 align:middle line:90%
And he said, who knows?

00:05:15.000 --> 00:05:19.470 align:middle line:84%
That's the place, the
who knows, who knows.

00:05:19.470 --> 00:05:23.370 align:middle line:84%
And usually when you
have gotten attached

00:05:23.370 --> 00:05:27.690 align:middle line:84%
to the spiritual, material
experiences of bliss,

00:05:27.690 --> 00:05:31.200 align:middle line:84%
and of intimacy, and of
aliveness of spirit, when

00:05:31.200 --> 00:05:35.790 align:middle line:84%
it turns dead, and cold, and
nothing, you get so freaked,

00:05:35.790 --> 00:05:38.700 align:middle line:84%
and so reactive, and
feeling like you fell out

00:05:38.700 --> 00:05:43.620 align:middle line:84%
of grace that you are then
dealing with all your reactions

00:05:43.620 --> 00:05:46.230 align:middle line:84%
to it, not with
the thing itself,

00:05:46.230 --> 00:05:48.150 align:middle line:90%
just with the reactions to it.

00:05:48.150 --> 00:05:49.980 align:middle line:90%
With, oh, I wasn't worthy.

00:05:49.980 --> 00:05:50.910 align:middle line:90%
I didn't deserve it.

00:05:50.910 --> 00:05:53.460 align:middle line:90%
Oh, see, God figured me out.

00:05:53.460 --> 00:05:56.240 align:middle line:90%
I'm a fraud, you know?

00:05:56.240 --> 00:06:01.070 align:middle line:84%
And now because I've gone in
and out of it so many times,

00:06:01.070 --> 00:06:03.170 align:middle line:90%
now my faith is strong.

00:06:03.170 --> 00:06:05.570 align:middle line:84%
Not my faith that I
will feel the experience

00:06:05.570 --> 00:06:09.830 align:middle line:84%
of being close to God, but
just the faith of that it is.

